file=Cybersecurity/veil/operational/commands/veil-commands.md · tb=\| Trigger phrases \| Skill \| Shortcut \| · tb=\|---\|---\|---\| · tb=\| "classify," "data classification," "what tier," "sensitivity label" \| data-classification \| /veil-classify \| · tb=\| "privacy," "DPIA," "data protection," "GDPR," "privacy by design" \| privacy-by-design \| /veil-privacy \| · tb=\| "DLP," "data loss," "exfiltration," "egress," "data leak" \| data-loss-prevention \| /veil-dlp \| · tb=\| "breach notification," "GDPR 72h," "notify regulator," "PIPEDA" \| breach-notification \| /veil-notify \| · p:Precedence=1. **Classification first.** Before DLP monitoring or breach notification, data must be classified. Unclassified data gets default INTERNAL treatment.\n2. **DLP alert with confirmed exfiltration** → breach-notification (check clocks). DLP confirms the leak; breach-notification handles the regulatory obligation.\n3. **Any notification** → operator/legal approval required before sending. veil drafts; operator approves and sends.\n4. **All gaps** (unclassified data, DLP blind spots, unclear jurisdictions) → warden's register.\n